# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Public brand configuration — SAFE TO COMMIT (no secrets here).
# Fill these in with the `/setup-project` command, or edit by hand.
# Left blank, the template ships unbranded and shows neutral placeholders.
#
# NOTE: these are Vite build-time vars — the dev server / build must
# reload to pick up changes (Vite restarts automatically on .env edits).
#
# Secrets (ADMIN_PASS / AUTH_PASS for the preview gate) do NOT belong here.
# Set those in Vercel's Environment Variables, or a local .env.local (ignored).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Fills the primary name, e.g. the "Deep Focus Review" part of the title.
VITE_SITE_NAME=""

# Fills the secondary label, e.g. the "Refinements" part of the title.
VITE_SITE_SUBTITLE=""

# Fills the site tagline shown in the masthead/header. Optional.
VITE_SITE_TAGLINE=""

# ── Phase II marker ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Set to "true" once the styleguide has been configured for this project
# (fonts & colors set in the token layer, example sections adapted). While
# blank/false, a setup banner shows on the styleguide page. See /setup-styleguide.
VITE_STYLEGUIDE_READY=""
